Rating: 3
A very nice dish for those who are counting calories - even with the pasta, this is a tasteful, sensible dinner. As some here suggested, I concentrated the clam reserve before proceeding with the dish, and thought the result was flavorful. As an extra touch, I added some roasted red pepper in addition to the tomatos - yum.

Rating: 3
This receipe is good as is, but with a couple of additions was great. First, substitute 1 Tbs butter, 1/4 C white wine and 2 cloves minced garlic for the water. After the clams (mussels are good too) open, remove clams and boil liquid down until reduced by 1/2. Add another 1 Tbs butter, remaining 1 garlic clove and 1/8 Cup cream along with the other ingredients. Wonderful as a main or even a side along fillet.

