Rating: 4
This is the absolute tastiest linguine with clams I have ever tried. I no longer have to order it in restaurants. I will try cooking down the liquid next time like another reviewer suggested becuase there was a lot of liquid.

Rating: 4
I doctored this recipe quite a bit: first, I soaked the clams in cold water so that they released sand (which they released quite a lot of). Next, I found that the liquid left after steaming the clams was a lot more than what I started with so I boiled it down to concentrate the clam flavor. Then, I added a little butter to the clam juice and sauteed the tomatoes, basil, garlic etc. briefly. It was absolutely delicious this way; I made it for a family birthday dinner and it was very well-received, even by my non-pasta fan husband.

Rating: 3
This was a delicious recipe and light and low fat too! I also used a little bit of tomato sauce to coat the pasta, and the clams were absolutely wonderful!

Rating: 3
Tasty dish. The fresh clams have it all over canned clams or bottled clam juice. When I make this again, I will use a little tomato sauce to thicken the sauce and coat the pasta.